\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Side-by-side summary of the three stages on the species-disjoint Pantera test set. v4.3-singlefold is the only variant whose train and validation species are disjoint for the whole run. In particular, the 0.919 DNA/hAT score in v4.3 collapses to 0.256 under the single-fold protocol, and to 0.265 in v4.2, which essentially share the same archetecture and training protocol except using per-superfamily sample size capping at 3{,}000. This effectly results in different trainval sets being used in all three runs. }}{22}{table.caption.29}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:stage_compare}{{7}{22}{Side-by-side summary of the three stages on the species-disjoint Pantera test set. v4.3-singlefold is the only variant whose train and validation species are disjoint for the whole run. In particular, the 0.919 DNA/hAT score in v4.3 collapses to 0.256 under the single-fold protocol, and to 0.265 in v4.2, which essentially share the same archetecture and training protocol except using per-superfamily sample size capping at 3{,}000. This effectly results in different trainval sets being used in all three runs}{table.caption.29}{}}
